properties.areaDesc: South Laramie Range Foothills; Central Laramie Range and Southwest Platte County
properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued February 7 at 6:09PM MST until February 8 at 5:00PM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
* WHAT...West winds 30 to 40 mph with gusts up to 65 mph expected.
Areas of blowing snow that could reduce visibilities under a
half mile at times.

* WHERE...Central Laramie Range and Southwest Platte County and
South Laramie Range Foothills Counties.

* WHEN...From 5 AM to 5 PM MST Saturday.

* IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. Hazardous travel conditions
with blowoff and or blowover risks High to Extreme. Areas of
blowing and drifting snow likely to produce low visibility and
slick roads. Travel will be difficult especially for
lightweight, high profile vehicles and campers.
properties.instruction:
People are urged to secure loose objects that could be blown
around or damaged by the wind.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 5 AM TO 5 PM MST SATURDAY
